Field Label: Is one of the patient's household members an essential worker? According to the U..S Department of Homeland Security, essential workers are those who conduct a range of operations and services that are typically essential to continue critical infrastructure operations. Critical infrastructure is a large, umbrella term encompassing sectors from energy to defense to agriculture. Examples of essential workers: health care, food service, public transportation, public safety officers and first responders, and electricity industry.

Field Label: Other KD clinical features, please describe:

Definitions:

Hypovolemic shock: dehydration with reduced intravascular volume
Distributive shock: reduced peripheral vascular resistance (vasodilation)
Cardiogenic shock: reduced cardiac output (pump failure)
